node.title: Victoria records 905 new local COVID-19 cases and 4 deaths
node.alt: A Melbourne laneway in wet weather.
node.description: There are now 17,302 active cases of the virus, and 411 people have died during the current Delta outbreak in the state.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 905\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and four\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 17,302\u00a0active cases of the virus, and 411\u00a0people have died during the current Delta outbreak in the state.\u00a0", "There are\u00a0394\u00a0people in hospital in Victoria with COVID-19, of whom 75\u00a0are in intensive care and 46\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 72\u00a0people are in intensive care but their COVID-19 infections are no longer active.", "The new cases were identified from 64,218\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 8,498\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.\u00a0", "", "
How to take a rapid antigen test.
"]
